title: Get the latest from F1 launch week here
text:
F1 Get the latest from F1 launch week here This is how F1 will look in 2017 and we have reactions from around the paddock and beyond. By Alexandra McCarthy on 21 February 2017 
After what feels like a very long winter break, pre-season testing for 2017 is just around the corner. 
But before F1 jets off to testing in Barcelona, we round up the best reactions during launch week. R.S.17 The shark fin on the RS17 attracts the eye © Renault Sports 
Less yellow, more black. There's no doubt that Renault's 2017 car looks bigger and badder than last year. 
However all the attention seems to have fallen on the driver's race suits. They will certainly be turning a few heads on the grid this year... Drivers just walked in wearing new race suits. Interesting. pic.twitter.com/7jcOfFHTNl — Will Buxton (@thebuxtonblog) February 21, 2017 Fashion alert. Looks like Renault makes the same mistake twice. pic.twitter.com/XFmnd7PLHZ — Parc Fermé (@PFF1) February 21, 2017 Sauber C36 The new C36 features a blue and gold livery © Sauber The C36, the new Sauber car © Sauber The Swiss team is celebrating its 25th anniversary © Sauber 
No doubt the Sauber C36 will glimmer on the grid with the gold lining they've added to their livery. Sauber driver Marcus Ericsson is definitely a fan of his "new office". A post shared by Marcus Ericsson (@ericsson_marcus) on Feb 20, 2017 at 4:11am PST Williams FW40
